{
  "texts": [
    "The execution starts with determining the overall macroeconomic conditions across countries and asset classes, exploring the riskand-return characteristics of asset classes.",
    "This analysis determines the capital allocation across countries and asset classes (\"tactical asset allocation\").",
    "Security analysis enables the cross-sectional selection of single securities within each asset class to construct the overall portfolio and execute the necessary trades.",
    "Finally, after the portfolio experienced the market dynamics of an investment period, the feedback layer evaluates past performance, updates the market conditions, checks if the investment policy still holds or needs to be adjusted, and finally rebalances the portfolio (Bailey et al., 2007; Horn and Oehler, 2020).",
    "Portfolio construction has been a significant task since 1952 when Markowitz introduced the mean-variance model."
  ]
}